  "body": "The second step in the migration process to moving to StatusQ components, is to use the layout framework provided by StatusQ. \r\n\r\nThis entails a bunch of things:\r\n\r\n1. Make use of `StatusAppLayout` which holds a `StatusAppNavBar`\r\n1. Ensure community tab buttons are properly dynamically added\r\n1. Also ensure app section switch continues to work\r\n1. App layout also expects `StatusAppTwoPanelLayout` components for its views, so all \"app sections\" (Chat, community, profile, wallet etc) should use that component on their most outer level. This means we have to touch all `*Layout` components that live in Status Desktop at the moment\r\n\r\nLast but not least: there's a bunch of app section specific functionality and components attached to `AppLayout` that are expected to exist throughout the entire application (another thing that needs a refactor, but we leave that for another step). \r\n\r\nThose specific functionalities need to continue to work, so let's make sure we don't break anything.",
